stopher Woodruff的女兒，於1352年出生在英國薩默塞特瑟其姆爾。她於1370年與Sir Thomas Wheatley在英國坎布利其爾結婚。他們至少是1個兒子的父母。她去世於1410年在英國英格蘭薩默塞特瑟其姆爾享年58歲，埋葬在英國英格蘭薩默塞特瑟其姆爾。"},"zh-hans":{"1352–1410":"1352年–1410年","1350–1410":"1350年–1410年","1375–1472":"1375年–1472年","1325–Male":"1325年–殁","1325":"1325年","1410":"1410年","1375":"1375年","1352":"1352年","1472":"1472年","1350":"1350年","1382":"1382年","1370":"1370年","Wooley, Sedgemoor, Somerset, England":"英国英格兰薩默塞特瑟其姆爾","Wooley, Cambridgeshire, England":"英国坎布利其爾","Wooley, Sedgemoor, Somersetshire, England":"英国英格兰薩默塞特瑟其姆爾","lifeSummary":"Mary Woodruff是Christopher Woodruff的女儿，于1352年出生在英国薩默塞特瑟其姆爾。她于1370年与Sir Thomas Wheatley在英国坎布利其爾结婚。他们至少是1个儿子的父母。她去世于1410年在英国英格兰薩默塞特瑟其姆爾享年58岁，埋葬在英国英格兰薩默塞特瑟其姆爾。"},"hr":{"1352–1410":"1352.–1410.","1350–1410":"1350–1410.","1375–1472":"1375.–1472","1325–Male":"1325–preminuo","1325":"1325","1410":"1410.","1375":"1375.","1352":"1352.","1472":"1472","1350":"1350","1382":"1382","1370":"1370.","Wooley, Sedgemoor, Somerset, England":"Sedgemoor, Somerset, Engleska, United Kingdom","Wooley, Cambridgeshire, England":"Cambridgeshire, England","Wooley, Sedgemoor, Somersetshire, England":"Sedgemoor, Somerset, Engleska, United Kingdom"},"cs":{"1352–1410":"1352–1410","1350–1410":"1350–1410","1375–1472":"1375–1472","1325–Male":"1325–Zesnulý","1325":"1325","1410":"1410","1375":"1375","1352":"1352","1472":"1472","1350":"1350","1382":"1382","1370":"1370","Wooley, Sedgemoor, Somerset, England":"Sedgemoor, Somerset, Anglie, United Kingdom","Wooley, Cambridgeshire, England":"Cambridgeshire, Anglie","Wooley, Sedgemoor, Somersetshire, England":"Sedgemoor, Somerset, Anglie, United Kingdom"},"da":{"1352–1410":"1352–1410","1350–1410":"1350–1410","1375–1472":"1375–1472","1325–Male":"1325–Afdød","1325":"1325","1410":"1410","1375":"1375","1352":"1352","1472":"1472","1350":"1350","1382":"1382","1370":"1370","Wooley, Sedgemoor, Somerset, England":"Sedgemoor, Somerset, England, United Kingdom","Wooley, Cambridgeshire, England":"Cambridgeshire, England","Wooley, Sedgemoor, Somersetshire, England":"Sedgemoor, Somerset, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1352–1410":"1352–1410","1350–1410":"1350–1410","1375–1472":"1375–1472","1325–Male":"1325–Overleden","1325":"1325","1410":"1410","1375":"1375","1352":"1352","1472":"1472","1350":"1350","1382":"1382","1370":"1370","Wooley, Sedgemoor, Somerset, England":"Sedgemoor, Somerset, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Wooley, Cambridgeshire, England":"Cambridgeshire, England","Wooley, Sedgemoor, Somersetshire, England":"Sedgemoor, Somerset, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1352–1410":"1352–1410","1350–1410":"1350–1410","1375–1472":"1375–1472","1325–Male":"1325–Deceased","1325":"1325","1410":"1410","1375":"1375","1352":"1352","1472":"1472","1350":"1350","1382":"1382","1370":"1370","Wooley, Sedgemoor, Somerset, England":"Sedgemoor, Somerset, England, United Kingdom","Wooley, Cambridgeshire, England":"Cambridgeshire, England","Wooley, Sedgemoor, Somersetshire, England":"Sedgemoor, Somerset, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Woodruff","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: from Middle English <i>woderove</i> ‘woodruff, sweet woodruff’ (Old English <i>wudurofe</i>), a sweet-scented plant. The leaves of the plant have a sweet smell and the surname may also have been a nickname for one who used it as a perfume, or perhaps an ironical nickname for a malodorous person. Alternatively, perhaps a topographic name for someone who lived at or near a place where woodruff grew. There may have been some confusion with   Woodrow  .","History: Two English families brought the name Woodruff to the American colonies: those of Matthew Woodruff and of John and Ann Woodruffe. The latter migrated to Lynn, MA, from Kent, and moved to Southampton, Long Island, NY, before 1640. John and Ann's many descendants were established in NJ, NC, and SC by 1790. The city of Woodruff, SC, is named for this family. The name is variously spelled Woodrove, Woodroffe, Woodruffe, Woodrough, and Woodruff in colonial records."],"variants":[{"name":"Woodroof","meanings":["English (London): variant of   Woodruff  ."]},{"name":"Woodrow","meanings":["English (Norfolk): from Middle English <i>wode</i> ‘wood’ + <i>reue</i> ‘row, row of houses’ (Old English <i>wudu</i> + <i>rǣw, rāw</i>). The surname may be topographic, for some who lived at or near a row of trees, or a row of houses within a wood, or it may be habitational, from any place so named, such as Wood Row in Hatfield Broad Oak (Essex) or Woodrow in Chaddesley Corbett (Worcestershire). There may have been some confusion with   Woodruff  ."]}]},{"name":"Mary","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Hebrew: Bitter; Marion is the French form."],"variants":[{"name":"Marion","meanings":["Originally a medieval French diminutive form of   Marie  , introduced to Britain in the Middle Ages. In some places it was taken as a pet form of   Margaret   or   Margery .  As a male name, it is an altered form of the Continental male name <i>Marian</i>, a derivative of Latin <i>Marianus</i> (from   Marius  ), but is now rarely, if ever, used. It was the birth name of the American film star  John Wayne  (  1907–79 )."]},{"name":"Marcia","meanings":["Often used as a feminine equivalent of   Mark  , but in fact a feminine form of <i>Marcius</i>, itself a derivative of   Marcus .  One  St Marcia  is commemorated in a group with Felix, Luciolus, Fortunatus, and others; another with Zenais, Cyria, and Valeria; and a third with Ariston, Crescentian, Eutychian, Urban, Vitalis, Justus, Felicissimus, Felix, and Symphorosa. None is individually very famous."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":30,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Mary Woodruff was born in 1352, in Sedgemoor, Somerset, England as the daughter of Christopher Woodruff. She married Sir Thomas Wheatley in 1370, in Cambridgeshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1410, in Sedgemoor, Somerset, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 58, and was buried in Sedgemoor, Somerset, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1352–1410":"1352–1410","1350–1410":"1350–1410","1375–1472":"1375–1472","1325–Male":"1325–Surnud","1325":"1325","1410":"1410","1375":"1375","1352":"1352","1472":"1472","1350":"1350","1382":"1382","1370":"1370","Wooley, Sedgemoor, Somerset, England":"Sedgemoor, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Wooley, Cambridgeshire, England":"Cambridgeshire, England","Wooley, Sedgemoor, Somersetshire, England":"Sedgemoor, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1352–1410":"1352–1410","1350–1410":"1350–1410","1375–1472":"1375–1472","1325–Male":"1325–Kuollut","1325":"1325","1410":"1410","1375":"1375","1352":"1352","1472":"1472","1350":"1350","1382":"1382","1370":"1370","Wooley, Sedgemoor, Somerset, England":"Sedgemoor, Somerset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Wooley, Cambridgeshire, England":"Cambridgeshire, England","Wooley, Sedgemoor, Somersetshire, England":"Sedgemoor, Somerset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1352–1410":"1352–1410","1350–1410":"1350–1410","1375–1472":"1375–1472","1325–Male":"1325–Décédé","1325":"1325","1410":"1410","1375":"1375","1352":"1352","1472":"1472","1350":"1350","1382":"1382","1370":"1370","Wooley, Sedgemoor, Somerset, England":"Sedgemoor, Somerset, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Wooley, Cambridgeshire, England":"Cambridgeshire, Angleterre","Wooley, Sedgemoor, Somersetshire, England":"Sedgemoor, Somerset, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Mary Woodruff est née en 1352, à Sedgemoor, Somerset, Angleterre, fille de Christopher Woodruff. Elle a épousé Sir Thomas Wheatley en 1370, à Cambridgeshire, Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils. Elle est décédée en 1410, à Sedgemoor, Somerset, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, à l’âge de 58 ans, et a été enterrée à Sedgemoor, Somerset, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni."},"de":{"1352–1410":"1352–1410","1350–1410":"1350–1410","1375–1472":"1375–1472","1325–Male":"1325–Verstorben","1325":"1325","1410":"1410","1375":"1375","1352":"1352","1472":"1472","1350":"1350","1382":"1382","1370":"1370","Wooley, Sedgemoor, Somerset, England":"Sedgemoor, Somerset, England, United Kingdom","Wooley, Cambridgeshire, England":"Cambridgeshire, England","Wooley, Sedgemoor, Somersetshire, England":"Sedgemoor, Somerset, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Mary Woodruff wurde 1352 in Sedgemoor, Somerset, England, als Tochter von Christopher Woodruff geboren. Sie hat 1370 in Cambridgeshire, England Sir Thomas Wheatley geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Sohn. Sie starb 1410 im Alter von 58 Jahren in Sedgemoor, Somerset, England, United Kingdom und wurde in Sedgemoor, Somerset, England, United Kingdom begraben."},"ht":{"1352–1410":"1352–1410","1350–1410":"1350–1410","1375–1472":"1375–1472","1325–Male":"1325–Desede","1325":"1325","1410":"1410","1375":"1375","1352":"1352","1472":"1472","1350":"1350","1382":"1382","1370":"1370","Wooley, Sedgemoor, Somerset, England":"Sedgemoor, Somerset, Angletè, United Kingdom","Wooley, Cambridgeshire, England":"Cambridgeshire, England","Wooley, Sedgemoor, Somersetshire, England":"Sedgemoor, Somerset, Angletè, United Kingdom"},"hu":{"1352–1410":"1352–1410","1350–1410":"1350–1410","1375–1472":"1375–1472","1325–Male":"1325–elhunyt","1325":"1325","1410":"1410","1375":"1375","1352":"1352","1472":"1472","1350":"1350","1382":"1382","1370":"1370","Wooley, Sedgemoor, Somerset, England":"Sedgemoor, Somerset, Anglia, United Kingdom","Wooley, Cambridgeshire, England":"Cambridgeshire, England","Wooley, Sedgemoor, Somersetshire, England":"Sedgemoor, Somerset, Ang